<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="138" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="138">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="138">
The shell morphology of the present specimens compare very well to 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Gastropoda" family="Scolodontidae" genus="Prohappia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Prohappia besckei" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="3" pageNumber="138" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="besckei">Prohappia besckei</taxonomicName>
; the size of the specimens from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Goiás">Goias</normalizedToken>
, however, is much smaller (D ~ 2 mm), slightly larger than half the normal size. This could represent a variation of the species in a cave environment, but the sample is too small to be of any significance. The present record extends the species distribution ca. 600 km to the north.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
